Now that you've learned a bit about Git and Github, reflect upon and answer the following questions.

What is the difference between Git and Github? Git is the system that lets you manage and track your code history, GitHub is a service that lets you manage repos which others can contribute to
Why use Git? // it is a software for tracking changes in files while developing source code during development
Why use Github? // to collaborate and work on code with others - can work on projects together from anywhere
What is the payoff to using Git and Github? // saves every version of code, projects can be worked on from anywhere with multiple contributors
